01:29.045 --> 01:33.528
♪ I'LL BE READY
[I'LL BE READY] ♪

01:33.702 --> 01:37.532
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR
[NO, DON'T YOU FEAR] ♪

01:37.706 --> 01:40.709
♪ I'LL BE READY ♪

01:40.883 --> 01:46.280
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS,
I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

01:46.454 --> 01:50.936
[THEME MUSIC]

02:07.431 --> 02:08.345
-THERE YOU ARE.

02:08.519 --> 02:09.912
OKAY, TAKE IT AWAY.

02:10.869 --> 02:15.831
[CROWD NOISE]

02:33.370 --> 02:35.459
-HEY, MY CLEVERNESS DOESN'T
STOP WITH INVENTIONS,

02:35.633 --> 02:37.069
I GOT ALL SORTS OF GREAT IDEAS

02:37.244 --> 02:39.376
ON HOW TO DO JUST
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

02:40.943 --> 02:41.900
-COME ON.

02:42.988 --> 02:44.164
[LAUGHING]

02:47.123 --> 02:49.038
-WHY DON'T YOU GET REALLY
CLEVER AND FAX YOUR LUNCH OVER.

02:49.212 --> 02:52.824
-FAX SNACKS, I LIKE IT.
IT'S GOT A NICE RING TO IT.

02:52.998 --> 02:55.305
[LAUGHING]

02:55.479 --> 02:56.654
-WE THOUGHT YOU
WERE GONNA PANIC

02:56.828 --> 02:58.787
IF YOU KNEW THAT THE ISLAND
WAS GOING UNDER WATER.

02:58.961 --> 03:00.528
-IT'S MY DUTY TO PROTECT
YOU, AFTER ALL I'M THE

03:00.702 --> 03:03.313
STRONG, SOLID
MALE AND YOU'RE THE
FRAIL HELPLESS FEMALE.

03:03.487 --> 03:05.663
-YES YOU BIG STRONG MAN YOU.

03:14.716 --> 03:16.935
-EDDIE, WHEN I LEFT
YOU AT HOME THIS MORNING

03:17.109 --> 03:18.110
YOU WERE WATCHING
GILLIGAN'S ISLAND,

03:18.285 --> 03:19.808
AND NOW YOU'RE WATCHING IT HERE.

03:19.982 --> 03:21.418
DON'T YOU THINK YOU'RE
JUST A LITTLE BIT FIXATED?

03:21.592 --> 03:23.551
-UH UH, IT'S A
DIFFERENT EPISODE.

03:23.725 --> 03:25.205
ON DIFFERENT CHANNELS
ALL DAY LONG.

03:26.423 --> 03:29.078
MOVE, YOU'RE BLOCKING MARY ANN!

03:32.995 --> 03:35.867
-WE MUST GET ORGANIZED.
HOW ARE WE GOING TO STAY AFLOAT?

03:36.041 --> 03:37.782
-WHY DON'T WE BUILD
AN ARK LIKE NOAH DID?

03:37.956 --> 03:39.306
-THAT'S A WONDERFUL IDEA.

03:39.480 --> 03:41.046
WE'LL TAKE THE RAFT THE
MEN STARTED TO BUILD

03:41.221 --> 03:42.570
A COUPLE OF MONTHS AGO AND
WE'LL PUT A NEW HUT ON IT.

03:43.397 --> 03:45.050
-GOD, LOOK AT GINGER.

03:45.225 --> 03:47.270
ALL THOSE YEARS ON THE SAME
ISLAND WITH THE SAME DRESS

03:47.444 --> 03:48.880
AND SHE STILL LOOKS FANTASTIC.

03:51.361 --> 03:53.407
-HOW LONG HAVE THEY
ALL BEEN SITTING THERE?

03:53.581 --> 03:56.279
-TOO LONG, MUCH TOO LONG.
THEIR EYES HAVE GLAZED OVER.

03:56.453 --> 03:57.367
-THANK YOU.

03:57.933 --> 04:00.892
[LAUGHTER]

04:01.066 --> 04:02.459
-HEY, YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE IN UNIFORM PAL.

04:02.633 --> 04:04.156
-YEAH, YEAH, YEAH
NEXT COMMERCIAL.

04:04.331 --> 04:05.810
-GARNER, I'M SURPRISED
AT YOU WATCHING THIS.

04:05.984 --> 04:07.986
-HEY LOOK, I JUST SAT
DOWN TO TIME MY SHOE.

04:08.160 --> 04:09.945
-YEAH OKAY, WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE ALL STOP WATCHING GILLIGAN

04:10.119 --> 04:11.468
AND DO WHAT WE'RE
SUPPOSED TO BE DOING, HUH?

04:11.642 --> 04:13.209
[SHOUTING]

04:13.383 --> 04:15.298
-COME ON, DON'T
TOUCH THAT DIAL.

04:15.472 --> 04:17.474
THIS IS MY FAVORITE EPISODE.
IT'S THE ONE WHERE

04:17.648 --> 04:20.346
THE PROFESSOR THINKS THE
ISLAND IS SINKING SO HE DEVISES

04:20.521 --> 04:22.740
THIS BRILLIANT SCHEME TO BUILD
A BOAT AND THEN THEY SPLIT

04:22.914 --> 04:25.003
JUST BEFORE THE TIDE
GOES OUT. IT'S GREAT.

04:25.177 --> 04:26.614
[LAUGHING]

04:26.788 --> 04:28.398
-DID I MISS A
MEETING OR SOMETHING?

04:28.572 --> 04:30.966
-AH NO CAPTAIN, WE WERE JUST

04:31.140 --> 04:33.055
CHECKING OUT THE
STORM REPORT THERE.

04:33.229 --> 04:36.450
-THE WEATHER STARTED
GETTING ROUGH.

04:37.015 --> 04:38.234
-ALL I SEE IS SUNSHINE.

04:38.408 --> 04:40.454
FIGURING OUT HOW TO
SPEND ALL MY MILLIONS.

04:40.628 --> 04:43.152
-OH COME ON, CAPTAIN, YOU'VE
BEEN BUYING A LOTTERY TICKET

04:43.326 --> 04:45.154
EVERY WEEK FOR THE
LAST TWO YEARS.

04:45.328 --> 04:46.547
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
YOU'RE GONNA WIN THIS TIME?

04:46.721 --> 04:48.375
-PERSISTENCE PAYS OFF.

04:48.549 --> 04:50.202
BESIDES, WOULD I HAVE ANY
CHANCE IF I DIDN'T BUY A TICKET?

04:50.377 --> 04:53.597
-THERE IS SOME
LOGIC THERE CAPTAIN.

04:54.250 --> 04:56.339
-WHAT'S THE JACKPOT
UP TO NOW CAPTAIN?

04:56.513 --> 04:58.036
-70 MILLION DOLLARS.

04:58.210 --> 04:59.603
THE LINES WERE AROUND THE BLOCK,

04:59.777 --> 05:01.866
70 MILLION, AND IT'S
ALL GONNA BE MINE.

05:02.911 --> 05:04.956
-MOVE OVER THURSTON HOWELL.

05:05.566 --> 05:07.350
-FORGET GILLIGAN'S
ISLAND WILL YOU?

05:07.524 --> 05:09.352
WE GOT A WHOLE BEACH
LOAD OF PEOPLE OUT THERE

05:09.526 --> 05:11.093
WHO NEED TO BE RESCUED.

05:19.144 --> 05:22.191
-29 MINUTES. MAN, YOU GUYS
AT DOMINOS ARE UNBELIEVABLE.

05:23.671 --> 05:26.456
YES, HERE YOU GO.
KEEP THE CHANGE, MIKE.
SEE YOU AROUND BUD.

05:32.244 --> 05:35.857
-YOU GONNA EAT THAT
ALL BY YOURSELF?

05:36.031 --> 05:36.727
-MAYBE.

05:38.163 --> 05:39.774
[LAUGHTER]

05:39.948 --> 05:41.384
GO AHEAD MAN, HELP YOURSELF.

05:43.517 --> 05:46.955
-SO, GILLIGAN'S ISLAND WAS
REALLY YOUR FAVORITE TV SHOW?

05:47.129 --> 05:50.175
-WAS? MAN IT STILL
IS, ALWAYS WILL BE.

05:51.829 --> 05:53.657
-EVERYBODY'S GO THEIR
OWN TASTE I GUESS.

05:56.312 --> 06:00.751
-I DON'T KNOW, GROWING UP AN
ORPHAN NEVER HAVING A FAMILY

06:02.405 --> 06:03.711
THOSE SEVEN PEOPLE
ON THAT ISLAND

06:03.885 --> 06:05.452
BECAME MY FAMILY GARNER,

06:06.627 --> 06:08.193
THEY WERE ALWAYS THERE
FOR ME. WHAT CAN I SAY?

06:08.368 --> 06:09.586
-GILLIGAN'S ISLAND?

06:10.370 --> 06:11.936
-YES, GILLIGAN'S ISLAND.

06:12.110 --> 06:13.416
-YOU REALLY DID HAVE IT
ROUGH DIDN'T YOU LITTLE BUDDY?

06:13.590 --> 06:14.983
-CHEAP SHOT MAN.

06:15.157 --> 06:19.901
-[LAUGHING] THANKS, NEXT
TIME GET SOME NAPKINS.

06:20.554 --> 06:22.382
GOTTA GO.
WHOA!

06:22.556 --> 06:24.296
-HEY, HEY, HEY WATCH YOURSELF.

06:25.080 --> 06:26.255
-THANKS.

06:32.348 --> 06:33.262
-HEY!

06:34.394 --> 06:34.959
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY!

06:37.614 --> 06:39.181
COME ON, BREAK IT UP WOULD YA?

06:41.444 --> 06:42.445
GET A ROOM.

06:43.403 --> 06:44.839
WHOA!

06:49.452 --> 06:50.453
-EDDIE, YOU OKAY?

06:54.283 --> 06:55.110
YOU OKAY?

06:55.719 --> 06:56.764
-WHAT? YEAH.

06:57.286 --> 06:59.680
I'M FINE, I'M A
LITTLE EMBARRASSED.

06:59.854 --> 07:00.768
-I THOUGHT IT WAS LIFEGUARDS

07:00.942 --> 07:02.247
WHO WERE SUPPOSED TO SAVE LIVES.

07:02.422 --> 07:03.423
-VERY FUNNY.

07:04.424 --> 07:05.599
-SURE YOU OKAY NOW?

07:06.338 --> 07:08.776
-YEAH, YEAH, I'M FINE.

07:10.212 --> 07:11.474
THANKS.

07:17.437 --> 07:19.961
-RESCUE ONE,
THIS IS KMF 295, OVER.

07:20.135 --> 07:21.528
-THIS IS RESCUE ONE.

07:21.702 --> 07:23.704
-MCCLAIN, WE'VE GOT A
REPORT OF A WAVE RUNNER

07:23.878 --> 07:25.445
OUT OFF THE OCEAN
SIDE OF ANACAPA.

07:25.619 --> 07:27.272
-WHAT'S HE DOING THAT FAR OUT?

07:27.969 --> 07:30.188
-GO PICK UP KRAMER AT TOWER
15 AND CHECK IT OUT, OVER.

07:30.362 --> 07:32.103
-WILL DO, OVER AND OUT.

07:32.930 --> 07:37.805
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

07:51.993 --> 07:53.298
-STRAIGHT AHEAD, SEE IT?

07:53.473 --> 07:54.474
-YEAH.

07:58.260 --> 08:00.436
-ALL RIGHT, NOW TRY AND PULL
IT AS CLOSE AS YOU CAN.

08:07.530 --> 08:08.618
HEY.

08:08.792 --> 08:10.620
-THANK GOD YOU GUYS SHOWED UP.

08:10.794 --> 08:11.752
-WHAT'S WRONG?

08:11.926 --> 08:13.318
-I DON'T KNOW, MY ENGINE DIED

08:13.493 --> 08:14.929
AND I JUST CAN'T SEEM
TO GET IT TO KICK OVER.

08:15.103 --> 08:16.365
-LET ME GIVE YOU A HAND.
SEE WHAT I CAN DO.

08:18.106 --> 08:20.195
WHY DON'T YOU SLIDE
UP A LITTLE BIT.

08:21.805 --> 08:22.893
I DON'T KNOW HOW
ELSE TO DO THIS?

08:23.067 --> 08:24.591
-THIS WAY SEEMS FINE.

08:28.986 --> 08:30.814
-PUT THIS BACK IN THERE.

08:32.033 --> 08:32.990
ALL RIGHT, LET'S SEE
SOMETHING HERE.

08:33.164 --> 08:35.123
WHY DON'T YOU PUSH
THIS BUTTON HERE,

08:35.297 --> 08:37.342
GIVE IT A LITTLE GAS AT
THE SAME TIME, READY?

08:37.517 --> 08:39.039
OH HEY, THERE WE GO.

08:39.214 --> 08:41.346
YOU KNOW WHAT IT WAS?
THE KILL SWITCH WAS STUCK.

08:42.130 --> 08:44.393
ALL RIGHT, YOU WANNA
RIDE BACK WITH US?

08:44.567 --> 08:47.396
-UM, NO I DON'T THINK SO.

08:47.570 --> 08:48.571
THANKS FOR THE START THOUGH.

08:48.745 --> 08:49.920
-NO PROBLEM.

08:50.704 --> 08:51.618
GIVE ME A HAND?

08:53.968 --> 08:55.056
HAVE A GOOD ONE.

08:59.930 --> 09:00.975
WHAT?

09:02.759 --> 09:04.152
CRANK IT UP AND LET'S GET GOING.

09:07.416 --> 09:09.070
COME ON.

09:09.244 --> 09:10.593
-IT WON'T START. I DON'T
KNOW WHAT'S THE MATTER.

09:13.335 --> 09:14.597
-HUH.

09:14.771 --> 09:15.772
-WHY DON'T YOU RADIO FOR HELP?

09:17.469 --> 09:20.821
-RESCUE ONE TO BAYWATCH,
REPEAT RESCUE ONE TO BAYWATCH.

09:24.041 --> 09:25.608
RADIO'S DEAD.

09:25.782 --> 09:27.567
IT'S THE ELECTRICAL SYSTEM.

09:27.741 --> 09:29.307
-WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

09:29.481 --> 09:32.615
-THERE'S NOT MUCH WE CAN DO.
WE JUST, I DON'T KNOW.

09:32.789 --> 09:34.835
THERE'S ANACAPA ISLAND,
WE'LL DRIFT TO THE SHORE

09:35.009 --> 09:36.358
AND WAIT FOR SOMEONE TO MISS US.

09:36.532 --> 09:37.794
-GREAT.

09:38.621 --> 09:40.754
-YOU KNOW, THERE IS
A BRIGHT SIDE TO THIS.

09:41.755 --> 09:42.799
THERE IS.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.236
COME ON, IT'S ROMANTIC,
THINK ABOUT IT.

09:45.410 --> 09:49.240
IT'S JUST YOU,
ME, THE MOON, HUH?

09:49.414 --> 09:51.199
-WELL ARE YOU SURE
YOU WOULDN'T RATHER BE

09:51.373 --> 09:52.461
STUCK ON THE ISLAND WITH
THE GIRL ON THE WAVE RUNNER?

09:52.635 --> 09:53.767
-I WAS JUST DOING MY JOB.

09:53.941 --> 09:54.942
-A LITTLE TOO WELL.

09:56.639 --> 09:58.989
COME ON, LIGHTEN UP.

09:59.816 --> 10:00.948
-YOU LIGHTEN UP.

10:03.603 --> 10:08.346
[WHIMSICAL MUSIC]

10:41.379 --> 10:42.598
-WELL...

10:45.775 --> 10:48.299
IF YOU WANT YOU CAN
START A SIGNAL FIRE

10:48.473 --> 10:50.127
AND I'LL LOOK FOR FOOD,
OR I CAN START A FIRE

10:50.301 --> 10:51.694
AND YOU CAN GO LOOK FOR FOOD.

10:51.868 --> 10:52.956
-I'LL START THE FIRE AND
YOU LOOK FOR THE FOOD.

10:53.130 --> 10:54.349
-THOUGHT YOU'D SAY THAT.

10:55.916 --> 11:00.921
[WHIMSICAL MUSIC]

11:23.073 --> 11:23.813
-HEY!

11:23.987 --> 11:25.554
-WHOA, UH OH.

11:27.599 --> 11:28.688
-GILLIGAN?

11:29.776 --> 11:31.603
WAIT! WAIT, GILLIGAN!

11:35.477 --> 11:37.871
GILLIGAN! HEY!

11:38.045 --> 11:39.394
HEY, GILLIGAN!

11:40.656 --> 11:41.962
HEY, WAIT UP.

11:45.530 --> 11:47.750
[PANTING]

11:49.099 --> 11:50.535
HEY GILLIGAN!

11:52.581 --> 11:56.237
[PANTING]

11:57.586 --> 11:59.849
HEY, COME ON I'M
YOUR BIGGEST FAN.

12:05.812 --> 12:07.161
WHERE'D THAT COME FROM?

12:10.294 --> 12:11.774
-WHOA!

12:16.561 --> 12:19.042
-GILLIGAN, MAN
IT REALLY IS YOU.

12:19.216 --> 12:20.391
-IT'S ME ALL RIGHT.

12:21.958 --> 12:23.264
WHOA!

12:23.438 --> 12:24.787
-YOU'RE HANGING OFF A CLIFF.

12:26.136 --> 12:27.268
-NOT FOR LONG.

12:32.882 --> 12:36.059
WHOA, HELP.

12:40.411 --> 12:41.673
-AM I GLAD TO SEE YOU.

12:41.848 --> 12:43.153
-WELL I'M
KINDA GLAD TO SEE YOU TOO,

12:43.327 --> 12:44.111
WHOEVER YOU ARE.

12:44.285 --> 12:45.242
-I'M EDDIE.

12:45.416 --> 12:46.635
I'M ON THE ISLAND WITH SHAUNI.

12:46.809 --> 12:47.723
AND--

12:47.897 --> 12:49.638
-LOOK OUT!

12:52.815 --> 12:55.252
HELP! HELP!

12:55.426 --> 12:57.646
-YOU KNOW WHAT?
MAYBE WE SHOULD YELL TOGETHER.

12:57.820 --> 12:58.690
-GOOD IDEA.

12:58.865 --> 13:00.605
TOGETHER!

13:00.780 --> 13:03.391
-NO, NO, NO. IT'S NO USE.
SHAUNI WILL NEVER HEAR US.

13:03.565 --> 13:06.350
-I'M NOT YELLING FOR SHAUNI.
I'M YELLING FOR MARY ANN!

13:06.524 --> 13:07.699
-MARY ANN?

13:09.658 --> 13:11.007
-I'M RIGHT HERE.

13:12.139 --> 13:15.620
-OH MAN, MARY ANN AND
GILLIGAN ALL IN THE SAME DAY.

13:15.795 --> 13:17.144
MUST BE MY BIRTHDAY.

13:20.277 --> 13:22.192
OH BOY.
GILLIGAN, DON'T LOOK DOWN.

13:23.672 --> 13:25.761
-HERE, LET ME HELP.

13:26.544 --> 13:28.764
GIVE ME YOUR HAND, COME ON.

13:31.332 --> 13:32.681
-DON'T LET GO.

13:36.293 --> 13:38.687
-YOU MEAN YOU GUYS
WERE REALLY SHIPWRECKED

13:38.861 --> 13:40.471
WITH THE HOWELLS,
AND THE SKIPPER,

13:40.645 --> 13:41.908
AND THE MOVIE STAR,
AND THE PROFESSOR?

13:42.082 --> 13:43.300
-YUP, THAT'S ALL OF US.

13:43.474 --> 13:45.085
-I THOUGHT YOU
WERE JUST A TV SHOW.

13:45.259 --> 13:47.000
-WE'RE REALLY
GLAD YOU FOUND US.

13:47.174 --> 13:49.263
FOR YEARS PEOPLE HAVE BEEN
GETTING ON AND OFF THE ISLAND

13:49.437 --> 13:50.873
AND WE WERE STUCK UNTIL NOW.

13:51.047 --> 13:52.048
-SO WHERE'S EVERYBODY ELSE?

13:52.222 --> 13:53.745
-STILL ON THE OTHER ISLAND.

13:53.920 --> 13:55.356
THE PROFESSOR FINALLY
WAS ABLE TO BUILD A BOAT,

13:55.530 --> 13:57.140
BUT IT WAS SO SMALL ONLY
TWO OF US COULD GET IN IT.

13:57.314 --> 13:58.402
-AND HERE WE ARE,
ON ANOTHER ISLAND,

13:58.576 --> 14:00.274
A MILLION MILES FROM NOWHERE.

14:00.448 --> 14:02.537
-SOON AS BAYWATCH SEES OUR SIGNAL FIRE
WE'RE AS GOOD AS HOME.

14:02.711 --> 14:03.930
-YOU MEAN THEN WE'RE RESCUED?

14:04.104 --> 14:05.366
-WE'RE FINALLY RESCUED?

14:05.540 --> 14:07.063
-THEY WILL BE HERE BY
TOMORROW TO PICK US UP

14:07.237 --> 14:08.325
AND THEY'LL PICK YOU UP TOO.

14:08.499 --> 14:09.587
-OH.

14:10.371 --> 14:12.155
AND I OWE IT ALL TO YOU.

14:13.374 --> 14:15.028
-IT'S THE LEAST I
COULD DO MARY ANN.

14:16.725 --> 14:17.552
MARY ANN.

14:26.430 --> 14:28.650
EVERYBODY, LET ME
HAVE YOUR ATTENTION.

14:28.824 --> 14:32.045
IT IS MY PRIVILEGE TO INTRODUCE
GILLIGAN AND MARY ANN.

14:36.223 --> 14:38.138
-GILLIGAN AND MARY ANN?

14:38.312 --> 14:39.661
-HOW DO YOU DO?

14:39.835 --> 14:41.358
WHEN WE GOT YOUR RADIO
MESSAGE WE THOUGHT

14:41.532 --> 14:43.230
YOU'D BEEN OUT IN
THE SUN TOO LONG.

14:43.404 --> 14:44.753
-IT'S REALLY THEM.

14:44.927 --> 14:46.886
-I FEEL LIKE I'VE
KNOWN YOU ALL MY LIFE.

14:47.060 --> 14:47.974
MAY I CALL YOU LITTLE BUDDY?

14:48.148 --> 14:48.975
-SURE.

14:51.542 --> 14:53.327
-ON BEHALF OF L.A.
COUNTY LIFEGUARDS,

14:53.501 --> 14:54.850
WELCOME TO BAYWATCH
HEADQUARTERS.

14:56.504 --> 14:58.549
-WOW, THIS
PLACE IS REALLY FANCY.

15:01.901 --> 15:06.601
-UH, CAPTAIN,
WHAT HAPPENED HERE?

15:06.775 --> 15:08.472
-70 MILLION DOLLARS
HAPPENED HERE,

15:08.646 --> 15:10.213
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED HERE.

15:10.387 --> 15:11.606
-YOU ACTUALLY WON
70 MILLION DOLLARS?

15:11.780 --> 15:13.782
-GOOD THINGS HAPPEN
TO THOSE WHO BET.

15:13.956 --> 15:18.526
-UH, GILLIGAN AND MARY ANN, LET
ME INTRODUCE CAPTAIN THORPE.

15:19.135 --> 15:20.876
-FROM ONE FAMOUS PERSON
TO OTHER FAMOUS PEOPLE

15:21.050 --> 15:22.617
IT IS A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

15:22.791 --> 15:24.793
-WELL I DON'T
KNOW ABOUT FAMOUS,

15:24.967 --> 15:26.664
BUT THINGS ARE SURE DIFFERENT
THAN THEY WERE 25 YEARS AGO.

15:26.838 --> 15:28.971
-THINGS ARE SURE DIFFERENT
THAN THEY WERE YESTERDAY.

15:29.145 --> 15:31.843
-THERE'S SO MUCH TO SEE.
SO MUCH HAS GONE ON.

15:32.757 --> 15:36.500
-WELL, I COULD SHOW YOU
AROUND IF YOU WANT ME TO.

15:36.674 --> 15:38.850
-OH YES, I'D LIKE THAT.

15:42.071 --> 15:45.074
-AMAZING, WITHOUT
ANY LUXURY WHATSOEVER

15:45.248 --> 15:46.946
YOU MANAGED TO SURVIVE.

15:47.120 --> 15:48.556
-WELL THE HUMAN APPETITE

15:48.730 --> 15:51.080
FOR SYNDICATED TELEVISION
IS INDOMITABLE.

15:51.254 --> 15:52.560
-YOU'RE RIGHT, I'M HUNGRY

15:52.734 --> 15:54.083
I CAN'T WAIT FOR A
HAMBURGER AND FRIES.

15:54.257 --> 15:56.346
-HAMBURGER AND FRIES ARE
LOADED WITH CHOLESTEROL.

15:56.520 --> 15:58.479
-WELL NOTHING FANCY.
I'LL JUST TAKE KETCHUP.

16:07.009 --> 16:10.230
-I CAN'T BELIEVE HOW THESE
BATHING SUITS HAVE CHANGED

16:10.404 --> 16:12.101
SINCE I'VE BEEN ON THE ISLAND.

16:12.275 --> 16:13.146
-LOT OF THINGS HAVE CHANGED

16:13.320 --> 16:14.930
SINCE YOU WERE STUCK
ON THAT ISLAND.

16:16.627 --> 16:18.238
-WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT EDDIE?

16:19.195 --> 16:21.241
-I JUST, I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

16:21.415 --> 16:22.590
YOU, HERE.

16:24.070 --> 16:26.681
-I CAN'T BELIEVE IT
EITHER, YOU'RE A REAL HERO.

16:26.855 --> 16:28.857
I'VE BEEN WAITING
FOREVER TO BE RESCUED,

16:29.031 --> 16:31.773
AND THEN YOU CAME ALONG.
IT'S LIKE A DREAM COME TRUE.

16:31.947 --> 16:34.645
-NO, NO IT'S NOT LIKE
A DREAM COME TRUE,

16:35.298 --> 16:37.039
IT IS A DREAM COME TRUE.

16:52.272 --> 16:55.405
-BE CAREFUL MY DEAR,
THAT'S EXPENSIVE CRYSTAL.

16:55.579 --> 16:57.799
AH, CHAMPAGNE
SERVICE FOR EVERYONE.

16:57.973 --> 16:59.670
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN I WOULD
LIKE TO WELCOME YOU ALL

16:59.844 --> 17:02.630
TO MY NEW LITTLE
BOAT, THE MINNOW II.

17:02.804 --> 17:05.067
WE ARE HERE TO
CELEBRATE MANY THINGS.

17:05.241 --> 17:06.808
FIRSTLY AND FOREMOSTLY,

17:06.982 --> 17:10.377
MY NEWLY ACQUIRED,
ENORMOUS WEALTH.

17:10.550 --> 17:12.031
SECONDLY, THE RESCUE
OF OUR GOOD FRIENDS,

17:12.204 --> 17:13.771
GILLIGAN AND MARY ANN.

17:13.944 --> 17:16.773
AND THIRDLY, MY PURCHASE
OF GILLIGAN'S RIGHTS

17:16.948 --> 17:19.907
TO THE SHIPWRECK TO BE
TURNED INTO A MINI-SERIES.

17:20.082 --> 17:23.564
OF COURSE WE DO NEED A
DRAMATIC UPBEAT ENDING

17:23.738 --> 17:27.872
TO THE SAGA OF THE
CASTAWAYS' ORDEAL, AND THAT

17:28.047 --> 17:31.093
IS THE REASON FOR OUR LITTLE
EXCURSION THIS AFTERNOON.

17:31.702 --> 17:35.228
WE ARE GOING TO RESCUE
THE OTHER CASTAWAYS.

17:35.402 --> 17:36.707
[CHEERING]

17:36.881 --> 17:38.013
MARY ANN MY DEAR,
PLEASE COME ABOARD.

17:38.187 --> 17:39.754
-OH, THANK YOU CAPTAIN THORPE.

17:39.928 --> 17:45.455
-GARNER, YOU WERE IN THE NAVY.
YOU'RE THE SKIPPER.

17:46.587 --> 17:48.241
-[LAUGHING]

17:53.159 --> 17:54.682
GANGWAY!

17:55.248 --> 17:56.858
-I'M SURE AN OLD NAVY MAN

17:57.032 --> 18:00.035
WILL BE UNIQUELY
FAMILIAR WITH OUR WATERS.

18:00.209 --> 18:04.474
EDDIE, SINCE YOU NEVER
FINISHED HIGH SCHOOL,

18:04.648 --> 18:05.780
YOU'RE THE FIRST MATE.

18:09.479 --> 18:11.046
-SKIPPER!

18:11.220 --> 18:14.876
-AND NOW, LET'S BE OFF BEFORE
INTEREST RATES COME DOWN.

18:15.050 --> 18:15.659
-WELL SAID.

18:17.052 --> 18:22.231
[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

18:26.714 --> 18:28.846
-SHAUNI?
-EY GAD.

18:30.892 --> 18:33.112
-CAPTAIN THORPE, I HEARD
ABOUT THE MINI-SERIES

18:33.286 --> 18:35.940
AND I WAS SO HOPING THERE
MIGHT BE A PART IN IT FOR ME.

18:36.115 --> 18:39.596
-WELL WE'LL SEE MY LITTLE
BEACH BOTTOM, WE'LL SEE.

18:39.770 --> 18:41.163
-YOU NEVER WANTED
TO BE AN ACTRESS.

18:41.946 --> 18:44.688
-THINGS CHANGE, EDDIE,
AND BESIDES

18:44.862 --> 18:46.212
YOU ALREADY HAVE THE
GIRL OF YOUR DREAMS.

18:46.821 --> 18:48.083
-SHAUNI.

18:49.084 --> 18:52.043
-SKIPPER, IF YOU DON'T
MIND, HISTORY AWAITS.

18:52.218 --> 18:55.743
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

18:55.917 --> 18:56.831
GILLIGAN.

19:05.144 --> 19:07.885
-CAST OFF ALL LINES.

19:08.059 --> 19:08.712
-WHAT'S A LINE?

19:09.365 --> 19:11.454
-UNTIE THE ROPES.

19:17.156 --> 19:19.375
OH, GILLIGAN!

19:22.378 --> 19:25.903
-ALL: BYE!

19:26.077 --> 19:31.779
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

19:44.052 --> 19:46.054
-AH, THE THRILL OF THE
OPEN SEA, A BEAUTIFUL WOMAN,

19:46.228 --> 19:47.577
WHAT COULD BE MORE INVIGORATING?

19:47.751 --> 19:49.710
-IT'S VERY EXCITING
CAPTAIN THORPE.

19:49.884 --> 19:51.712
-I FOUND THE INERTIAL
NAVIGATION SYSTEM

19:51.886 --> 19:54.105
TO BE QUITE IMPRESSIVE ON BOARD.

19:54.280 --> 19:56.020
I THINK WITH SUCH AN
ARRAY WE SHOULD HAVE

19:56.195 --> 19:58.066
NO PROBLEM LOCATING
THE CASTAWAYS.

19:58.240 --> 20:00.808
-OH, INDEED, DIRECT FROM
NASA, VERY VERY EXPENSIVE.

20:00.982 --> 20:03.506
-I THINK I'LL GO INSIDE
AND DOUBLE CHECK THE CHARTS.

20:03.680 --> 20:04.768
-DO THAT.

20:18.304 --> 20:19.870
-CAPTAIN THORPE.
-YES.

20:20.044 --> 20:22.046
-I WAS WATCHING TV LAST
NIGHT AND ALL I COULD FIND ON

20:22.221 --> 20:24.614
WAS THESE LITTLE GUYS WITH
MUSTACHES GOING [SILLY NOISES].

20:24.788 --> 20:27.313
-THAT WASN'T TELEVISION,
THAT WAS A VIDEO GAME.

20:27.487 --> 20:29.228
-OH, AND THEN SOMEBODY
CHANGED THE CHANNEL

20:29.402 --> 20:30.272
AND THEY DIDN'T EVEN GET UP.

20:30.446 --> 20:31.491
-A REMOTE CONTROL DEVICE.

20:31.665 --> 20:33.362
-AH, THEN I SAW A YOUNG WOMAN

20:33.536 --> 20:35.843
AND SHE WAS WEARING HER
UNDERWEAR ON THE OUTSIDE.

20:36.017 --> 20:39.281
-THAT WAS MADONNA, A VERY
FAMOUS SINGING PERSON.

20:39.455 --> 20:41.196
-SHE OUGHT TO BE ABLE
TO AFFORD CLOTHES.

20:43.503 --> 20:45.200
-GILLIGAN. HEY, GILLIGAN!

20:47.420 --> 20:48.072
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

20:48.247 --> 20:49.335
-YOU JUST DID.

20:51.250 --> 20:52.860
-HOW LONG HAVE
YOU KNOWN MARY ANN?

20:53.034 --> 20:54.818
-WELL YOU KNOW, WE WERE
MAROONED ON AN ISLAND

20:54.992 --> 20:56.733
FOR 25 YEARS, AND YOU
GET TO KNOW SOMEBODY

20:56.907 --> 20:58.300
PRETTY GOOD THAT WAY.

20:58.474 --> 21:01.347
-YEAH, WELL I'VE ONLY
MET HER FOR ONE DAY NOW

21:01.999 --> 21:03.914
AND, WELL, I THINK...

21:04.480 --> 21:05.873
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO SAY THIS...

21:06.047 --> 21:07.266
-WELL, WHEN WE DIDN'T
KNOW HOW TO SAY ANYTHING

21:07.440 --> 21:08.745
WE ALWAYS ASKED THE
PROFESSOR, THEN HE'D SAY IT

21:08.919 --> 21:10.094
AND NOBODY'D UNDERSTAND IT.

21:11.531 --> 21:13.228
-RIGHT, YEAH WELL, ANYWAY.

21:14.229 --> 21:16.797
WELL I GUESS THE ONLY WAY TO
SAY IT IS TO JUST TELL YOU.

21:18.799 --> 21:19.974
I LOVE MARY ANN.

21:20.844 --> 21:22.063
-YOU LOVE MARY ANN?

21:22.237 --> 21:24.065
-WELL, I THINK I DO.
I THINK I DO.

21:24.239 --> 21:25.762
WHAT DO YOU THINK SHE'D
SAY IF I TOLD HER?

21:25.936 --> 21:27.329
-IF I WERE YOU
I WOULDN'T DO IT.

21:27.503 --> 21:29.070
-YOU WOULDN'T?
-NO, IF I WERE ME I'D DO IT.

21:29.244 --> 21:31.159
-YOU? WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU LOVE MARY ANN?

21:31.333 --> 21:32.769
-YEAH.

21:32.943 --> 21:34.597
-YOU WERE ON AN ISLAND
WITH HER FOR 25 YEARS

21:34.771 --> 21:35.903
AND YOU NEVER TOLD HER?

21:36.077 --> 21:37.470
-WELL THE TIMING
NEVER SEEMED RIGHT

21:37.644 --> 21:38.384
BUT NOW THAT YOU'VE
BROUGHT IT UP,

21:38.558 --> 21:40.168
I THINK I'LL TELL HER RIGHT NOW.

21:40.342 --> 21:44.912
[THUNDER]
UH OH.

21:46.522 --> 21:48.263
-GILLIGAN! GILLIGAN, EDDIE!

21:48.437 --> 21:49.612
BATTEN DOWN THE HATCHES,

21:49.786 --> 21:51.353
WE'VE GOT ROUGH
WEATHER APPROACHING.

21:51.527 --> 21:53.529
THERE'S A BIG STORM COMING!

21:54.443 --> 21:55.575
-I HOPE WE PACKED THE BATTENS.

21:55.749 --> 21:56.793
-I'LL
GO HELP THE SKIPPER.

21:56.967 --> 21:58.055
-RIGHT BEHIND YA.

21:58.229 --> 22:02.669
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

22:13.636 --> 22:16.291
-SEE, THERE SHE BLOWS!

22:16.944 --> 22:21.252
WE CAN'T OUTRUN IT.
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE TO SAIL
RIGHT INTO THE EYE OF THE STORM.

22:21.427 --> 22:23.516
EVERYBODY, HOLD ON!

22:29.043 --> 22:32.786
GILLIGAN, GO BELOW AND
BREAK OUT THE LIFE JACKETS.
-AYE AYE, SKIPPER.

22:32.960 --> 22:35.049
BATTEN DOWN SOME
HATCHES OR SOMETHING.

22:35.223 --> 22:39.488
[BLOWING WIND]

22:48.584 --> 22:50.194
I GOT YA, GILLIGAN.

23:00.727 --> 23:01.945
DON'T LET GO.

23:02.119 --> 23:04.121
GET HIM. SOMEBODY GRAB HIS LEGS.

23:04.774 --> 23:06.297
SET HIM DOWN, SET HIM DOWN.

23:06.472 --> 23:11.955
[BLOWING WIND]

23:18.658 --> 23:21.661
I THOUGHT WE LOST YOU
THERE LITTLE BUDDY.

23:26.927 --> 23:29.582
-COULD BE WORSE!
COULD BE RAINING!

23:31.975 --> 23:35.022
-OH YOU HAD TO SAY IT.
YOU HAD TO SAY IT.

23:35.196 --> 23:38.765
[BLOWING WIND]

23:41.376 --> 23:45.467
-HANG ON.
HANG ON. CAREFUL.

23:46.250 --> 23:49.123
SHAUNI. SHAUNI, GET BACK.
GET BACK.

23:58.437 --> 24:02.049
I CAN'T HOLD IT.

24:11.754 --> 24:13.495
-SHIPWRECKED AGAIN.

24:13.669 --> 24:16.063
-WELL AT LEAST WE'RE ALL SAFE.
THAT'S THE IMPORTANT THING.

24:16.890 --> 24:19.109
-SKIPPER, WHAT ARE WE
GOING TO DO?

24:19.283 --> 24:22.243
I JUST BOUGHT MY FIRST
CORPORATION, THORPE CORP,

24:22.417 --> 24:24.114
AND I SO WANTED TO BE
THERE. THIS MORNING,

24:24.288 --> 24:26.029
THEY'RE PUTTING MY
NAME ON THE DOOR.

24:26.769 --> 24:28.118
-WHAT ABOUT THE MOVIE?

24:28.292 --> 24:30.425
THEY COULD GIVE MY
PART TO SOMEBODY ELSE.

24:30.599 --> 24:32.645
-YOU'LL GET USED TO
THAT BEING SHIPWRECKED.

24:34.385 --> 24:35.082
-WHAT WAS THAT?

24:35.256 --> 24:36.866
-YOU'LL GET USED TO THAT TOO.

24:44.265 --> 24:46.615
♪ JUST SIT RIGHT BACK
AND YOU'LL HEAR A TALE ♪

24:46.789 --> 24:48.399
♪ A TALE OF A FATEFUL TRIP ♪

24:48.574 --> 24:50.576
♪ THAT STARTED FROM
THIS TROPIC PORT ♪

24:50.750 --> 24:53.056
♪ ABOARD THIS TINY SHIP ♪

24:53.230 --> 24:55.102
♪ THE MATE WAS A
MIGHTY SAILING MAN ♪

24:55.276 --> 24:56.930
♪ THE SKIPPER BRAVE AND SURE ♪

24:57.104 --> 24:59.323
♪ FIVE PASSENGERS
SET SAIL THAT DAY ♪

24:59.498 --> 25:04.067
♪ FOR A THREE HOUR
TOUR, A THREE HOUR TOUR ♪

25:04.241 --> 25:05.982
[THUNDER]

25:06.156 --> 25:07.506
♪ THE WEATHER
STARTED GETTING ROUGH ♪

25:07.680 --> 25:09.595
♪ THE TINY SHIP WAS TOSSED ♪

25:09.769 --> 25:12.511
♪ IF NOT FOR THE COURAGE
OF THE FEARLESS CREW ♪

25:12.685 --> 25:16.384
♪ THE MINNOW WOULD BE LOST,
THE MINNOW WOULD BE LOST ♪

25:16.558 --> 25:18.517
♪ THE SHIP SET GROUND
ON THE SHORE OF THIS ♪

25:18.691 --> 25:20.736
♪ UNCHARTED DESERT ISLE ♪

25:20.910 --> 25:22.956
♪ WITH GILLIGAN ♪

25:23.130 --> 25:25.001
♪ THE SKIPPER TOO ♪

25:25.175 --> 25:29.440
♪ THE MILLIONAIRE AND HIS WIFE ♪

25:29.615 --> 25:31.704
♪ A MOVIE STAR ♪

25:31.878 --> 25:34.663
♪ THE PROFESSOR AND MARY ANN ♪

25:34.837 --> 25:37.187
♪ HERE ON GILLIGAN'S ISLE ♪

25:38.798 --> 25:42.105
-I SUGGEST THAT WE BUILD SOME
FORM OF SHELTER SINCE I SEE

25:42.279 --> 25:44.151
NO WAY OF DETERMINING
OUR PRECISE LOCATION

25:44.325 --> 25:46.153
WITHOUT CONDUCTING A
SYSTEMATIC SURVEILLANCE.

25:46.327 --> 25:47.894
-HARVEY'S RIGHT.
LET'S BUILD SHELTER.

25:48.068 --> 25:49.460
-WON'T THAT TAKE A LONG TIME?

25:49.635 --> 25:51.245
-NOT IF WE UTILIZE OUR
INDIVIDUAL ABILITIES

25:51.419 --> 25:53.160
TO MAXIMIZE OUR EFFORTS.

25:53.334 --> 25:54.901
FOR INSTANCE, SKIPPER,
WHAT I WANT YOU TO DO

25:55.075 --> 25:55.989
IS GET THE SAW
FROM THE MINNOW II

25:56.163 --> 25:57.251
TO CUT DOWN SOME
LOGS FROM TREES.

25:57.425 --> 25:59.383
GILLIGAN? GILLIGAN. YOU HELP HIM.

25:59.558 --> 26:02.430
EDDIE, GATHER SOME
HEMP FOR ROPES.
-RIGHT.

26:02.604 --> 26:04.258
-SHAUNI WHAT I
WOULD LIKE YOU TO DO

26:04.432 --> 26:07.304
IS TO GATHER SOME PALM FRONDS
AND GIVE THEM TO MARY ANN

26:07.478 --> 26:09.742
TO WEAVE THEM TOGETHER
FOR WALL PANELS WITH THE HEMP.

26:09.916 --> 26:11.570
-OH, I'VE ALWAYS
BEEN GOOD AT HEMP.

26:11.744 --> 26:13.702
MR. THORPE.

26:13.876 --> 26:18.533
-I'M UPPER MANAGEMENT.
VERY VERY UPPER MANAGEMENT
I MIGHT ADD.

26:18.707 --> 26:20.840
-FINE, YOU SUPERVISE.

26:21.014 --> 26:24.191
EVERYBODY ELSE, LET'S GET TO IT.

26:25.888 --> 26:28.935
COME ON LITTLE BUDDY, SHAUNI.

26:29.109 --> 26:30.240
-WHAT'S HEMP?

26:33.635 --> 26:36.029
-GILLIGAN, WE BETTER
GET BUSY ON THESE LOGS.

26:36.203 --> 26:37.857
WE'VE GOTTA GET THE HUT
BUILT BEFORE NIGHTFALL.

26:40.860 --> 26:41.730
OH, GILLIGAN!

26:41.904 --> 26:47.257
[LIVELY MUSIC]

27:55.978 --> 27:58.372
-OKAY, GILLIGAN, LOWER THE ROOF.

28:14.823 --> 28:16.042
[APPLAUSE]

28:16.216 --> 28:17.696
-WELL DONE, LAD. WELL DONE.

28:19.393 --> 28:20.437
-HOW'S ANYBODY
GONNA FIT IN THERE?

28:20.611 --> 28:21.482
-IT'S BIGGER INSIDE.

28:21.656 --> 28:23.136
-HUH?
-TRUST ME.

28:42.155 --> 28:43.069
-GOODNIGHT CAPTAIN THORPE.

28:45.419 --> 28:46.725
-NIGHT NIGHT MY BOY.

28:54.645 --> 28:55.821
-NIGHT HARVEY.

28:57.692 --> 28:58.475
-GOODNIGHT EDDIE.

29:03.698 --> 29:05.526
-YOU KNOW SOMETHING
GILLIGAN, YOU WERE RIGHT,

29:05.700 --> 29:07.354
IT'S A LOT BIGGER INSIDE
THAN IT IS OUTSIDE.

29:07.528 --> 29:08.398
-TOLD YA.

29:10.009 --> 29:14.013
-GET TO BED LITTLE BUDDY.
LOT OF WORK TO DO TOMORROW.

29:14.665 --> 29:16.189
-I KNOW WHAT HIS PROBLEM IS.
HE PROBABLY WANTS A STORY.

29:16.363 --> 29:18.017
THE SKIPPER ALWAYS
TOLD ME A STORY.

29:18.191 --> 29:20.541
I MUST HAVE HEARD JACK AND
THE BEANSTALK 10,000 TIMES.

29:20.715 --> 29:21.977
YOU KNOW THE STORY WHERE
JACK CLIMBS A BIG BEANSTALK
HE GOT FROM THE MAGIC BEANS

29:22.151 --> 29:24.197
WHICH HE PLANTED FROM THE COW?

29:24.371 --> 29:25.241
AND THEN ALL OF A SUDDEN
HE MEETS THE GIANT
WHO SCARES HIM AND GOES...

29:25.415 --> 29:27.287
-I KNOW THE STORY GILLIGAN!

29:28.157 --> 29:29.768
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?
A STORY, EDDIE?

29:29.942 --> 29:31.813
-WELL NO ACTUALLY.

29:33.032 --> 29:36.078
I KNOW GILLIGAN'S ISLAND
AND WELL I'M AFRAID IF I TRY

29:36.252 --> 29:38.341
TO CLIMB INTO THE TOP
SOMETHING MIGHT HAPPEN AND...

29:38.515 --> 29:40.300
-OH, NOTHING'S GOING TO HAPPEN.

29:40.474 --> 29:43.651
NOW, CLIMB UP THERE,
AND THAT'S AN ORDER.

29:44.565 --> 29:45.479
-OKAY.

29:47.960 --> 29:53.661
[YELLING]

29:59.188 --> 30:01.974
-WELL I GUESS I'M GONNA HAVE
TO GIVE YOU A HAND EDDIE.

30:11.026 --> 30:13.420
THERE YOU GO. SEE?
NOTHING IS GOING TO HAPPEN.

30:13.594 --> 30:14.203
-YEAH.

30:14.377 --> 30:16.162
-LET'S GET SOME SHUT-EYE.

30:27.086 --> 30:31.525
[CRASHING]
[YELLING]

30:49.325 --> 30:50.849
-I TOLD YOU
SOMETHING WOULD HAPPEN.

30:54.678 --> 30:57.333
MAROONED ON AN ISLAND.
THIS IS EXCITING.

30:57.507 --> 31:00.423
-MAYBE FOR YOU, I'M USED TO IT.

31:00.989 --> 31:01.555
YOU KNOW WHAT IS EXCITING?

31:01.729 --> 31:03.209
-WHAT?

31:03.383 --> 31:04.601
-WHAT YOU DO,
BEING A LIFEGUARD.

31:04.775 --> 31:07.387
-OH, IT'S A PIECE OF CAKE.
ANYBODY CAN DO IT.

31:08.388 --> 31:10.129
YEAH, DO YOU WANT
ME TO TEACH YOU

31:10.303 --> 31:11.608
MOUTH TO MOUTH RESUSCITATION?

31:11.782 --> 31:12.566
-COULD YOU?

31:12.740 --> 31:14.220
-SURE, SURE.

31:14.394 --> 31:16.613
-GILLIGAN, DO YOU THINK
I'LL MAKE A GOOD GINGER?

31:16.787 --> 31:18.615
-I DON'T KNOW. SHE
WAS ONE OF A KIND.

31:19.399 --> 31:20.661
-ALL THOSE YEARS ON THE ISLAND,

31:20.835 --> 31:21.836
DID YOU AND GINGER
EVER HAVE A THING?

31:22.010 --> 31:22.750
-WHAT KIND OF A THING?

31:22.924 --> 31:24.534
-WELL YOU KNOW, A THING.

31:24.708 --> 31:25.622
-OH, A THING.

31:25.796 --> 31:27.233
-WELL DID YOU?

31:27.407 --> 31:28.582
-NO, I KINDA LIKED MARY ANN.

31:28.756 --> 31:32.064
-OH, YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE!

31:33.326 --> 31:36.111
-OH NO, I NEVER TOLD HER HOW
I FELT AND NOW IT'S TOO LATE.

31:36.285 --> 31:37.721
-OH, NO, IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

31:37.896 --> 31:39.114
-WELL LOOK AT THEM.

31:39.898 --> 31:41.247
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

31:41.421 --> 31:42.596
-YOU'RE GONNA DO EXACTLY
WHAT SHE'S DOING TO YOU,

31:42.770 --> 31:43.684
YOU'RE GONNA MAKE HER JEALOUS.

31:43.858 --> 31:44.903
-HOW?

31:45.077 --> 31:46.861
-BY FIGHTING FIRE WITH FIRE.

31:49.995 --> 31:51.997
-YEAH, YEAH THAT'S IT.

31:52.171 --> 31:55.087
-THANK YOU EDDIE, THAT
WAS VERY INSTRUCTIVE.

31:55.261 --> 31:56.610
I CAN'T WAIT TO SHOW GILLIGAN.

31:56.784 --> 31:57.916
-GILLIGAN.

31:58.090 --> 32:00.222
YOU TWO HAVE SPENT A
LOT OF TIME TOGETHER,

32:00.396 --> 32:01.571
MUST BE PRETTY TIGHT.

32:02.094 --> 32:04.226
-IT'S KINDA FUNNY,
I NEVER TOLD HIM BEFORE,

32:04.400 --> 32:07.186
BUT I THINK I'M
IN LOVE WITH HIM.

32:07.751 --> 32:09.840
I WISH I KNEW IF HE FELT
THE SAME WAY ABOUT ME.

32:12.626 --> 32:15.324
WELL, I GUESS THAT
ANSWERS THE QUESTION.

32:21.243 --> 32:23.028
GILLIGAN! WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

32:23.202 --> 32:24.812
-I THINK IT'S FAIRLY OBVIOUS.

32:24.986 --> 32:26.553
-ARE YOU JEALOUS YET?

32:26.727 --> 32:27.771
-JEALOUS!

32:27.946 --> 32:30.078
WELL, I'LL SHOW YOU
HOW JEALOUS I AM.

32:33.603 --> 32:35.301
WELL, WHAT DO YOU THINK OF THAT?

32:35.475 --> 32:36.693
-I'LL SHOW YOU WHAT
HE THINKS OF THAT.

32:41.089 --> 32:43.048
-OH YEAH?
-YEAH!

32:53.580 --> 32:55.712
-I FORGOT TO MENTION, THIS
HOLE BREAKS TO THE LEFT.

32:57.801 --> 33:00.979
ALL THINGS CONSIDERED, IT
IS RATHER PEACEFUL HERE.

33:01.153 --> 33:02.937
-WHAT COULD HAPPEN
ON A DESERTED ISLAND?

33:03.111 --> 33:08.116
[YELLING "SKIPPER"]

33:10.945 --> 33:12.033
GILLIGAN!

33:12.207 --> 33:14.122
-EY GAD. I'M PUTTING!

33:14.296 --> 33:15.036
-THIS IS IMPORTANT.

33:15.210 --> 33:17.343
-SO IS THIS. IT'S FOR A BIRDIE.

33:17.517 --> 33:18.300
-WHAT'S GOING ON
HERE LITTLE BUDDY?

33:18.474 --> 33:20.694
-WE WANT YOU TO MARRY US.

33:20.868 --> 33:22.304
-MARRY YOU?

33:22.478 --> 33:24.741
-YES, YOU'RE THE CAPTAIN.
YOU CAN PERFORM THE CEREMONY.

33:25.568 --> 33:27.918
-ACCORDING TO MARITIME
LAW, YOU'RE RIGHT.

33:28.963 --> 33:30.443
CONGRATULATIONS!

33:30.617 --> 33:32.662
EDDIE, YOU STAND NEXT TO SHAUNI.

33:32.836 --> 33:34.447
-I'M NOT MARRYING HER.
I'M MARRYING HER.

33:34.621 --> 33:35.926
-YEAH, AND I'M MARRYING,
WHAT'S YOUR NAME AGAIN?

33:36.101 --> 33:37.276
-SHAUNI.
-SHAUNI.

33:37.450 --> 33:38.842
AND I LOVE HER
WITH ALL MY HEART.

33:39.017 --> 33:40.192
-YOU CAN'T MARRY THEM.
WE WERE HERE FIRST.

33:40.366 --> 33:41.280
-YEAH.

33:41.454 --> 33:42.629
-NO, NO WE WERE HERE FIRST.

33:44.196 --> 33:46.502
-STOP IT, STOP IT!

33:47.851 --> 33:50.332
JUST STAND NEXT TO WHOEVER
YOU'RE GOING TO MARRY.

33:52.247 --> 33:56.251
ALL RIGHT, BY THE
POWER VESTED IN ME...

33:56.425 --> 33:57.905
-NO, NO, WAIT, WAIT,

33:58.079 --> 33:59.820
YOU FORGOT TO ASK IF
THERE ARE ANY OBJECTIONS.

33:59.994 --> 34:01.691
-WHO WOULD HAVE ANY
OBJECTIONS CAPTAIN THORPE?

34:01.865 --> 34:02.779
-I DO.

34:03.780 --> 34:05.173
-WHO DO YOU WANT TO MARRY?

34:06.174 --> 34:08.393
-NOBODY, I'VE JUST
BUILT A BOAT, THOUGH.

34:08.568 --> 34:10.960
IT'S DOWN BY THE LAGOON AND
ACCORDING TO MY CALCULATIONS,

34:11.136 --> 34:12.614
THE TIDE IS JUST RIGHT.

34:12.789 --> 34:14.181
IF THE BOAT DOESN'T
LEAVE IMMEDIATELY,

34:14.356 --> 34:16.663
NO ONE WILL EVER
GET OFF THIS ISLAND.

34:25.628 --> 34:26.672
-I CAN'T WAIT.

34:31.243 --> 34:32.505
-GREAT LITTLE BOAT.

34:33.288 --> 34:35.943
-BUT IT'LL ONLY FIT TWO.

34:36.117 --> 34:37.510
-WELL, I'M SORRY SKIPPER,

34:37.684 --> 34:39.338
BUT IT'S THE BEST
THAT I COULD DO.

34:39.512 --> 34:42.036
I HAD TO MODIFY THE STRUCTURE
OF THE EXISTING DESIGN

34:42.210 --> 34:43.777
BY USING INDIGENOUS MATERIALS

34:43.951 --> 34:45.213
AND MINIATURIZED COMPONENTS.

34:45.387 --> 34:46.735
-WHERE DID THE MOTOR COME FROM?

34:46.909 --> 34:50.304
-WELL THE MINNOW II HAD
A 300 HORSEPOWER ENGINE,

34:50.478 --> 34:52.655
THE MINNOW III HAS
ONE HORSEPOWER.

34:52.829 --> 34:55.702
I MANAGED TO SALVAGE THE
UNDAMAGED VALVES AND PISTONS

34:55.876 --> 34:58.922
AND CREATE AN ENGINE
PROPORTIONATELY STALWART ENOUGH

34:59.097 --> 35:01.838
TO FERRY TWO PASSENGERS
TO CIVILIZATION AND
BRING BACK HELP.

35:02.012 --> 35:03.318
-HOW COME IT TOOK OUR PROFESSOR

35:03.492 --> 35:05.407
25 YEARS TO GET
US OFF OUR ISLAND?

35:06.495 --> 35:08.106
-I HAD MORE TO WORK WITH.

35:08.280 --> 35:10.282
-SO IT'S READY TO GO?

35:10.456 --> 35:12.110
-WELL SKIPPER, YES IT IS.

35:12.284 --> 35:15.678
THE ONLY QUESTION IS:
WHO IS PRIVILEGED TO GO?

35:15.852 --> 35:17.245
-OBVIOUSLY I AM.

35:18.159 --> 35:19.421
-WHY YOU?

35:20.030 --> 35:22.511
-'CAUSE I'M RICH. RICH
PEOPLE ARE ALWAYS PRIVILEGED.

35:22.685 --> 35:25.123
-I BELIEVE HE HAS A POINT THERE.

35:27.516 --> 35:31.129
-I THINK WE SHOULD DRAW STRAWS.
THAT'S WHAT'S FAIR.

35:31.651 --> 35:33.783
-FAIR? ALL RIGHT.

35:35.394 --> 35:37.526
-THE LONGEST STRAWS GO.

35:49.103 --> 35:51.627
WELL THE ONE'S WHO'VE BEEN
MAROONED THE LONGEST GET TO GO.

35:51.801 --> 35:53.412
THAT'S ONLY FAIR.

35:53.586 --> 35:54.978
-FAIR. NOT RIGHT.

35:55.588 --> 35:57.720
-WELL, ACCORDING
TO MY CALCULATIONS,

35:57.894 --> 35:59.722
THE TIDES ARE JUST RIGHT.

35:59.896 --> 36:02.160
I SUGGEST WE LAUNCH THE
MINNOW III IMMEDIATELY.

36:07.991 --> 36:12.996
[GROANING]

36:33.930 --> 36:34.975
-THERE'S SOMETHING
I MEANT TO TELL YOU.

36:35.149 --> 36:36.542
-WHAT'S THAT?

36:37.282 --> 36:40.589
-THAT GILLIGAN, HE'S
ONE HECK OF A GUY.

36:42.156 --> 36:44.202
-BETWEEN YOU AND
ME, I THINK SO TOO.

36:45.115 --> 36:48.031
IT'S NOT GONNA STOP YOU FROM
REMEMBERING ME THOUGH WILL IT?

36:48.554 --> 36:50.164
-I'LL NEVER FORGET YOU.

36:55.430 --> 36:56.431
THANK YOU.

36:57.563 --> 37:01.697
[SPUTTERING MOTOR]

37:07.703 --> 37:08.791
-PUSH! PUSH!

37:22.414 --> 37:23.371
-BYE!

37:23.545 --> 37:25.939
-BYE! WE'LL BE BACK! HAVE FUN!

37:26.896 --> 37:28.071
-TAKE CARE LITTLE BUDDY.

37:28.246 --> 37:29.159
-THERE THEY GO.

37:29.334 --> 37:31.292
-DON'T FORGET TO SEND HELP!

37:31.814 --> 37:33.251
-AND A CHANGE OF CLOTHES!

37:39.431 --> 37:41.955
-BYE! BYE EDDIE!

38:01.627 --> 38:02.584
-WELL, PERHAPS YOU CAN WHIP UP

38:02.758 --> 38:05.108
ANOTHER ONE OF
YOUR MANGO FRAPPES.

38:05.283 --> 38:07.154
-WELL AS LONG AS
YOU'RE NOT DRIVING.

38:07.807 --> 38:10.505
-EDDIE.
-YEAH SKIPPER?

38:11.027 --> 38:12.464
-WEREN'T YOU STANDING HERE?

38:13.291 --> 38:16.772
ISN'T THIS YOUR STRAW,
IT'S THE LONGEST.

38:17.599 --> 38:18.905
-YES IT WAS.

38:19.079 --> 38:20.733
-BUT I THOUGHT YOU
SAID YOU LOVED HER.

38:21.864 --> 38:22.865
-MAYBE I DID.

38:24.345 --> 38:25.607
MAYBE I ALWAYS WILL.

38:26.347 --> 38:28.958
THOUGH IT MAY NOT ADD
UP TO A HILL OF BEANS,

38:29.132 --> 38:30.786
IT'S BETTER OFF
THIS WAY SKIPPER.

38:30.960 --> 38:33.354
-OH, IT'S NOT THE END OF
THE WORLD LITTLE BUDDY.

38:33.528 --> 38:34.660
WE'LL BE RESCUED SOME DAY.

38:34.834 --> 38:37.140
WHY DON'T YOU CLIMB
UP A PALM TREE

38:37.315 --> 38:39.229
AND GET US SOME
COCONUTS FOR BREAKFAST.

38:39.404 --> 38:40.796
-AYE AYE SKIPPER.

38:43.669 --> 38:44.670
-PROFESSOR,
I HAVE AN IDEA.

38:47.150 --> 38:50.415
[CLUNKING]

38:59.989 --> 39:01.426
-HOW YOU FEELING LITTLE BUDDY?

39:03.123 --> 39:04.777
-YOU CALLED ME LITTLE BUDDY.

39:04.951 --> 39:06.169
-WELL THERE'S WORSE
THINGS HE COULD CALL YOU

39:06.344 --> 39:07.823
FOR SLIPPING ON
YOUR OWN TOWER RAMP.

39:07.997 --> 39:09.347
-YEAH. [GROANING]

39:09.521 --> 39:12.219
-YOU POOR THING, YOU
HAD US ALL VERY WORRIED.

39:14.613 --> 39:16.136
-I HAD THE WILDEST DREAM.

39:16.310 --> 39:18.007
-YOU HAD A DREAM, WELL
I'M STILL DREAMING.

39:18.181 --> 39:19.269
I WON THE LOTTERY.

39:19.444 --> 39:20.270
-YOU DID?

39:20.445 --> 39:22.142
-YUP, $58 WORTH.

39:22.316 --> 39:25.101
'COURSE I BOUGHT $60 WORTH
OF TICKETS, BUT IT'S A START.

39:25.798 --> 39:26.712
GLAD TO SEE YOU'RE
FEELING BETTER.

39:26.886 --> 39:27.930
-THANKS.

39:29.149 --> 39:30.890
-COME ON. LET'S GET YOU HOME.

39:31.064 --> 39:32.370
YOU'VE GOT A NASTY
BUMP ON YOUR HEAD.

39:36.199 --> 39:37.810
-AND YOU'RE NOT MAD AT ME?

39:37.984 --> 39:39.464
-WHY SHOULD I BE MAD AT YOU?

39:39.638 --> 39:41.466
JUST BECAUSE YOU WATCH TOO
MUCH GILLIGAN'S ISLAND?

39:41.640 --> 39:42.815
COME ON.

39:43.337 --> 39:44.033
-NO, IT'S...

39:51.606 --> 39:52.781
SHAUNI, WAIT...

40:04.314 --> 40:05.751
OH, WHAT A DAY.

40:14.890 --> 40:15.935
-NIGHT GUYS.

40:17.589 --> 40:19.721
-HEY, HEY.
-HEY, HEY, SEE YOU
TOMORROW BRIGHT AND EARLY.

40:19.895 --> 40:21.157
-COME WITH US
MITCH, WE'RE GONNA GO

40:21.331 --> 40:23.116
TO YOUR FAVORITE
CHINESE RESTAURANT.

40:23.769 --> 40:24.639
-COME ON MITCH,
WE'LL NEVER DECIDE

40:24.813 --> 40:26.162
WHAT TO ORDER WITHOUT YOU.

40:26.336 --> 40:27.773
-WHAT'S SO IMPORTANT YOU
GOTTA STICK AROUND HERE?

40:27.947 --> 40:28.774
-THANKS FOR THE
INVITE, BUT I GOT

40:28.948 --> 40:29.992
A HECK OF A LOT OF
PAPERWORK TO DO.

40:30.166 --> 40:31.777
BESIDES, IT'S PEACEFUL AND QUIET

40:31.951 --> 40:33.343
AROUND HERE WHEN
YOU'RE NOT HERE.

40:33.518 --> 40:34.606
-WE TRIED.

40:35.215 --> 40:36.172
-THANKS.

40:36.346 --> 40:37.696
-SEE YA.
-SEE YA.

40:42.048 --> 40:47.053
[WHISTLING GILLIGAN'S
ISLAND THEME]

40:54.539 --> 40:59.239
[GILLIGAN'S ISLAND THEME]

41:10.946 --> 41:15.951
[END THEME MUSIC]
